<!DOCTYPE html>
<html xmlns:th="http://www.thymeleaf.org">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8"/>
    <title>A4 Landscape Fixed Canvas</title>
    <style>
        /* ==========================================================================
           1. HARD CANVAS SIZING (FOR OPENHTMLTOPDF ENGINE)
           ========================================================================== */
        @page {
            size: 842pt 595pt; /* Sets strict A4 Landscape page dimensions */
            margin: 0;         /* Strips physical print margins so div fills 100% */
        }

        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        /* ==========================================================================
           2. BROWSER RESET & EMULATION
           ========================================================================== */
        html, body {
            margin: 0 !important;
            padding: 0 !important;
            width: 842pt !important;
            height: 595pt !important;
            page-break-inside: avoid;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            /* Browser fallback styling */
            background-color: #ffffff; 
        }

        /* ==========================================================================
           3. THE PDF ARTWORK CONTAINER (THE FIX)
           ========================================================================== */
        .pdf-page-canvas {
            /* Physically force the container to take up the full page dimensions */
            width: 842pt;
            height: 595pt;
            
            /* Apply your exact background color hex here so the PDF engine paints it */
            background-color: #a4c2db; /* Matches the blue-grey tint from image 1 */
            
            /* Restricts content from leaking or creating a page 2 */
            overflow: hidden; 
            page-break-inside: avoid;
            
            /* Add your baseline padding-left (58pt) and top margins here */
            padding: 40pt 58pt; 
        }

        /* ==========================================================================
           4. LAYOUT GRID MATRIX
           ========================================================================== */
        .header-table-wrapper {
            display: table;
            width: 100%;
        }

        .left-column {
            display: table-cell;
            width: 75%;
            vertical-align: top;
            text-align: left;
        }

        .right-column {
            display: table-cell;
            width: 25%;
            vertical-align: top;
            text-align: right;
        }

        /* ==========================================================================
           5. TYPOGRAPHY BOUNDARIES
           ========================================================================== */
        .main-title {
            font-size: 24pt;
            line-height: 26pt;
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #222222;
            margin: 0 0 8pt 0;
        }

        .subtitle {
            font-size: 14pt;
            line-height: 16pt;
            color: #333333;
            margin: 0 0 12pt 0;
        }

        .meta-text {
            font-size: 11pt;
            line-height: 14pt;
            margin: 0 0 4pt 0;
            color: #444444;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="pdf-page-canvas">
        
        <div class="header-table-wrapper">
            
            <div class="left-column">
                <div class="main-title">
                    Projection of your liquid assets - last financial plan - scenario
                </div>
                <div class="subtitle">
                    Conservative
                </div>
                <div class="meta-text" style="margin-top: 15pt; color: #555555;">
                    Based on your financial situation and your considerations the following projection of your liquid assets summarizes your financial plan before optimization.
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="right-column">
                <div class="meta-text" style="font-weight: bold;">
                    M. and J. Vollenw...
                </div>
                <div class="meta-text">
                    29 May 2026
                </div>
            </div>
            
        </div>

    </div>

</body>
</html>
